stylometry: Transportation problems are problems dealing with transporting hubs and effeciancy of traveling. usually a transportation problem would have many cities listed and a optimal route would be needed along with hubs in optimal places to make travel easier and more direct. Transshipment problems are problems dealing with a company shipping and recieving their products in order to get them to the customer in the most effeciant manner. Nodes, arcs, and flows are the terms describing the way the the materials are transported given a graph. Nodes describe the hubs and arcs describe the other sites, while the flows are the optimal route. A transshipment problem example is a company is transporting their made materials to three different countries and  needs to know the best way to do so. they would find out prices for shipping and the optimal places for  shipping headquarters.
